<paragraph id="77322F4AFFA3FFED7EFF476062A49BD2" blockId="7.[151,1437,1070,1349]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7EFF476063679B2F" bold="true" box="[151,267,1070,1096]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7F7A476060669B2F" authorityName="Momtazi &amp; Maghsoudlou" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Layeghi &amp; Momtazi" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[274,522,1070,1096]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Pleonexes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qeshmensis">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7F7A476060669B2F" box="[274,522,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Pleonexes qeshmensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as 
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7D2D4760665B9B2F" authorityName="Layeghi &amp; Momtazi" authorityYear="2018" box="[837,1079,1070,1096]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Ampithoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qeshmensis">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7D2D4760665B9B2F" box="[837,1079,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Ampithoe qeshmensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="131C52BBFFA3FFED7A08476067F49B2F" author="Layeghi, Y. &amp; Momtazi, F." box="[1120,1432,1070,1096]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" pagination="515" refId="ref2918" refString="Layeghi, Y. &amp; Momtazi, F. (2018) Ampithoe qeshmensis sp. nov. (Amphipoda: Ampithoidae), a new herbivorous amphipod from the Persian Gulf. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 98 (3), 515. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315416001545" type="journal article" year="2018">Layeghi &amp; Momtazi (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. However, based on the following characters, 
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7CF0471C61E09B0B" authorityName="Layeghi &amp; Momtazi" authorityYear="2018" box="[664,908,1106,1132]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Ampithoe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qeshmensis">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7CF0471C61E09B0B" box="[664,908,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Ampithoe qeshmensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7AAA471C675F9B0B" authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1857" box="[1218,1331,1106,1132]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Pleonexes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7AAA471C675F9B0B" box="[1218,1331,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Pleonexes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; reduced and round spur on peduncle of male uropod 1, expanded basis of pereopods 3 and 4, and prehensile pereopods 5–7.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77322F4AFFA3FFED7EAF47F067249A22" blockId="7.[151,1437,1070,1349]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7EAF47F063D29BBF" authorityName="Momtazi &amp; Maghsoudlou" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Layeghi &amp; Momtazi" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[199,446,1214,1240]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Pleonexes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qeshmensis">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7EAF47F063D29BBF" box="[199,446,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Pleonexes qeshmensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7CDC47F061E59BBF" authority="Momtazi &amp; Maghsoudlou, 2020" authorityName="Momtazi &amp; Maghsoudlou" authorityYear="2020" box="[692,905,1214,1240]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Pleonexes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nargessi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7CDC47F061E59BBF" box="[692,905,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">Pleonexes nargessi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7DE747F0618B9BBF" bold="true" box="[911,999,1214,1240]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5ECA4E23FFA3FFED7DE747F0618B9BBF" box="[911,999,1214,1240]" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the following character states (character states of 
<taxonomicName id="B08D54C9FFA3FFED7F5B47AD63C79B9B" authorityName="Momtazi &amp; Maghsoudlou" authorityYear="2020" box="[307,427,1251,1276]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampithoidae" genus="Pleonexes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nargessi">
<emphasis id="45F9F358FFA3FFED7F5B47AD63C79B9B" box="[307,427,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="438">P. nargessi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): palm of male gnathopod 2 with robust seta (without seta), first uropod with naked outer ramus (8 setae on outer ramus), first male gnathopod without defining angle (with a defining angle), the length ratio of flagellum to peduncle on the second male antenna is 1/2 (1/5), and prehensile P5-7 (simple).
</paragraph>
